===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|p}} – a person ({{zh-l|*人}}) carrying something. It is often simplified to {{zh-l|*㠯}} in pre-[[Qin]] ancient scripts. Today, the person is partly visible on the right (see also the stylization in [[从]]).

See also [[重]], in which a person is carrying a bag, [[央]], in which a person is carrying a pole, and [[年]], in which a person is carrying the harvest.

===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*ləʔ||to take; to fetch}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}; STEDT under PTB ''*la-k''). Cognate with {{och-l|式|model; form; rule}}, {{och-l|試|to test; to try}}.

